contracts.name: Name
contracts.title: Contracts
contracts.descRegenerationCredit: Regeneration Credit, token backed by the community's environmental regeneration impact.
contracts.descRcImpact: This contract is responsible for calculating the system impact and also the impact per token.
contracts.descRegenerator: This contract defines and manages the rules and data specific to 'Regenerator' users within the system. Regenerators are individuals, families, or groups providing ecosystem regeneration services to an area.
contracts.descRegeneratorPool: This contract manages the distribution of Regeneration Credit tokens as rewards to regenerators for their ecosystem regeneration service provided.
contracts.descInpector: This contract defines and manages the rules and data specific to 'Inspector' users within the system. Inspectors are primarily responsible for collecting data from regenerators.
contracts.descInspectorPool: This contract manages the distribution of Regeneration Credit tokens as rewards to inspectors for their inspection services provided, for counting trees and biodiversity of the Regenerators regeneration area.
contracts.descResearcher: This contract defines and manages the rules and data specific to 'Researcher' users within the system. Researchers are primarily responsible for the development of the project impact calculator, for the creation and improvement of evaluation methods and through submitting researches, which are subject to validation and penalty mechanisms.
contracts.descResearcherPool: This contract manages the distribution of Regeneration Credit tokens as rewards to researchers for their research and methodology improvement service provided.
contracts.descDeveloper: This contract defines and manages the rules and data specific to 'Developer' users within the system. Developers are primarily responsible for the development of the project through submitting development reports, which are subject to validation and penalty mechanisms.
contracts.descDeveloperPool: This contract manages the distribution of Regeneration Credit tokens as rewards to developers for their code development, primarily for the development of the system software.
contracts.descContributor: This contract defines and manages the rules and data specific to 'Contributor' users within the system. Contributors perform generic contributions to the project and are subject to validation and penalty mechanisms.
contracts.descContributorPool: This contract manages the distribution of Regeneration Credit tokens as rewards to contributors for their participation, primarily for providing general services services to the system, such as translation, community support, desgin, PR etc.
contracts.descActivist: This contract defines and manages the rules and data specific to 'Activist' users within the system. Activists are primarily responsible for inviting new Regenerators and Inspectors, and they earn rewards based on the approval of their invited users.
contracts.descActivistPool: This contract manages the distribution of Regeneration Credit tokens as rewards to activists for their participation, primarily for providing invitation services.
contracts.descSupporter: Manages the rules and data specific to Supporter users within the community.
contracts.descInspection: Manages the lifecycle of regeneration inspections, from request to realization and validation.
contracts.descInvitation: This contract manages the rules and logic for users to invite others into the community.
contracts.descCommunity: This contract serves as the central registry for user management within the community.
contracts.descVote: Defines the rules and logic for determining if a user is eligible to vote for invalidation.
contracts.descValidation: Responsible for reviewing and voting to invalidate users and resources.
contracts.descRcIndex: This contract handles the RegenerationIndexRules, used by the inspections to estimate the Regenerator impact and calculate the RegnerationScore. The system will have only two categories: Trees & Biodiversity.

actions.descApproveToPublish: To call the offset/publish functions, you must first call the approve function. Approve the SupporterRules for the number of tokens you want to publish/offset.

descActions.burnTokens: Compensate your environmental degradation by burning Regeneration Credit tokens. Burning tokens permanently removes them from circulation and increases your compensation certificate.
descActions.invite: Allows a user to attempt to invite another wallet to the community.
descActions.addDelation: Allows registered users (excluding Supporters) to report other users or resources that may require invalidation.
descActions.requestInspection: Regenerators agree to receive an inspector to assess their registered area. They can make an allowedInitialRequests number of requests without delay. After that, they must wait timeBetweenInspections blocks between requests. A hard limit of 12 total inspections is enforced.
descActions.acceptInspection: Inspectors must only accept inspections they are capable of performing, being aware of the safety risks and responsibilities. Accepting an inspection counts as a 'give-up' until realized. Inspectors can only accept one open inspection at a time and cannot inspect the same regenerator twice. They must also adhere to specific delays and security windows.
descActions.addResearch: Allows a registered researcher to publish a new 'research' report. A 'research' can be a new calculator item, a new methodology or improvement of current ones or a generic regeneration research.
descActions.addResearchValidation: Allows a voter to vote to invalidate a research.
descActions.addCalculatorItem: Allows a researcher to publish a calculator item, used by users to calculate degradation.
descActions.addContribution: Contributions can only be published if certain time conditions and user type requirements are met.
descActions.offset: Allows a supporter to burn tokens to compensate for a specific item's degradation, with a message to the community. Before calling this function, supporters must approve the SupporterRules contract to burn the tokens.
descActions.realizeInspection: Inspectors must evaluate the amount of trees and species of the regeneration area. How many trees, palm trees and other plants over 1m high and 3cm in diameter there is in the regenerating area? Justify your answer in the report. How many different species of those plants/trees were found? Each different species is equivalent to one unity and only trees and plants managed or planted by the regenerator should be counted. Justify your answer in the report. Max result of 200.000 trees and 300 biodiversity.
descActions.updateProfilePhoto: Allows a supporter to update their profile photo.
descActions.declareReduction: Allows a supporter to declare a reduction commitment for a specific calculator item.
descActions.addReportValidation: Allows a validator to vote to invalidate a specific development report. This process increments the validation count for the report and may trigger its invalidation.
descActions.addReport: Development reports can only be published if certain time conditions and user type requirements are met.
